--- !u!114 &1602767915
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1602767914}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 789220b4a4610d748bdda463f09778b6, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  tutorialSteps:
  - stepName: Movement
    tutorialText: Press W to move up, S to move down, A to move left and D to move
      right. You can also use your dash ability by pressing the space button! If
      you're moving you dash in the direction you're going. If you're standing still
      you dash in the direction of your cursor.
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  - stepName: Attacking And Mining
    tutorialText: 'By pressing and holding the left mouse button, you will shoot
      a laser which can damage enemies.

      By pressing and holding the right
      mouse button, you will shoot a laser which can mine ores.'
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  - stepName: Inventory
    tutorialText: By pressing the TAB key on your keyboard you can open your inventory.
      If you walk over an item you will pick it up if you have enough space. You
      can move the item (or the whole stack) around in your invetory by click&dragging
      with your left mouse button. If you don't release the item in any of the slots,
      you will drop it on the ground. If you have 2 or more pieces of the item (if
      stackable) you can right click on it to drop just one piece. If you right click
      on an consumable item you will consume it. You can close the inventory by clicking
      the TAB or ESC key.
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  - stepName: Crafting
    tutorialText: 'After you get access to some crafting recipes you can walk into
      the crafting pool and drop the required amount of certain items to craft the
      desired item. As soon as you walk out of the crafting pool the item will appear
      in your inventory.

      First, drop 2 of the "Test" items and walk out. Then
      drop the last "Test" item and the one that appeared in your inventory and walk
      out. You can than try to consume the SPEED UPGRADE'
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  - stepName: Game
    tutorialText: There is a day/night cycle going on. During the day time you can
      explore, craft or mine resources, but be sure to track the time because when
      night time comes monsters will start spawning based on the furthest area you've
      reached. The further you go the harder the monsters become to kill. They will
      attack the core but if you come close enough they will target you if you stay
      in the range. You can die as many times as you want, but if the heart dies
      you die permanently. You can prepare for # nights for the boss fight. On night
      # the boss will spawn.
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  - stepName: NPCs
    tutorialText: When you reach a new area make sure to talk to the NPC. He wil
      reveal a part of the story and some crafting recipes. You can revisit all the
      NPCs as many times as you want if you for example forget a recipe.
    tutorialImage: {fileID: 0}
    pauseGame: 1
    requiresInput: 1
  tutorialPanel: {fileID: 1779800479}
  tutorialText: {fileID: 1424733424}
  continuePrompt: {fileID: 1384107670}
  continueKey: 13
  continuePromptText: Press ENTER to continue...
